Congratulations - you and your PC survived the Indigo installation process!

You are using the bspwm window manager, which is very heavily focused on keyboard shortcuts.
Here are some of the most important ones to get you started - you can use the up and down keys to scroll through this list.
This file can be found in your home folder if you choose to come back later.

Note that these are the default keybindings, and you can change them later in the sxhkdrc config file.

window management:
    super + k: move focus up
    super + j: move focus down
    super + h: move focus left
    super + l: move focus right
    super + shift + k: move window up
    super + shift + j: move window down
    super + shift + h: move window left
    super + shift + l: move window right
    super + c: focus next window on screen
    super + shift + c: focus previous window on screen
    super + grave (`): focus last focused window
    super + q: close window
    super + shift + q: force kill window
    super + left square bracket ([): switch to previous workspace
    super + right square bracket (]): switch to next workspace
    super + shift + left square bracket ([): move window to previous workspace
    super + shift + right square bracket (]): move window to next workspace
    super + i: rotate window positions
    super + shift + i: rotate window positions (reverse)
    super + g: swap current window with largest window
    super + t: set window to tiled (default state)
    super + f: set window to floating
    super + shift + t: set window to pseudo-tiled
    super + shift + f: set window to fullscreen
    super + ctrl + k: preselect window up
    super + ctrl + j: preselect window down
    super + ctrl + h: preselect window left
    super + ctrl + l: preselect window right
    super + ctrl + (number): set preselect ratio
    super + ctrl + space: cancel preselection for this window
    super + ctrl + shift + space: cancel preselection for this workspace
    super + alt + h: expand window from top
    super + alt + j: expand window from bottom
    super + alt + k: expand window from left
    super + alt + l: expand window from right
    super + alt + shift + h: contract window from top
    super + alt + shift + j: contract window from bottom
    super + alt + shift + k: contract window from left
    super + alt + shift + l: contract window from right
    super + (arrow keys): move window

mouse:
    super + left click drag: move window
    super + right click drag: resize window
    
apps:
    super + enter: terminal (alacritty)
    super + e: file manager (thunar)
    super + d: firefox

utility:
    super + space: app launcher (rofi)
    super + x: lock screen
    super + shift + s: take screenshot

advanced:
    super + escape: reload hotkey daemon (sxhkd)
    super + alt + q: exit bspwm
    super + alt + r: restart bspwm
